{"overview":"A compact ternary waltz in B major distinguished by its graceful tonal architecture: diatonic excursions to the subdominant (E major) in the B section and a harmonically enriched A' that introduces modal mixture (iv), raised-II color, and chromatic inner-voice sequences before resolving definitively to the tonic. The piece's most distinctive feature is the subtle interplay between major and minor subdominant sonorities (IV/iv) woven throughout all sections, lending a gentle expressive shadow to an otherwise luminous B major palette.","cross_piece_tags":["ternary","arpeggiated_bass","pedal_point","modal_mixture","circle_of_fifths","lyrical","meditative","intimate"]}
